    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;Segment Routing (SR) leverages the source-routing paradigm.  A node steers a packet through a controlled set of instructions, called segments, by prepending the packet with an SR header.  In the MPLS data plane, the SR header is instantiated through a label stack.  This document specifies the forwarding behavior to allow instantiating SR over the MPLS data plane (SR-MPLS).&lt;/p&gt;</t>
